    • sortResources

      public static Resource[] sortResources​(Resource[] resources)
      Sort resources in a Resource array with its quantity and remove blank resource The order is: COIN, SERVANT, SHIELD, STONE. The resources array can be of a shorter size and still the returned array will be of size 4. If the resources array is null, will be returned null.
      Parameters:
      resources - input array with the resources to sort
      Returns:
      the sorted array or null if the input is null

    • sumResources

      public static Resource[] sumResources​(Resource[] resources1, Resource[] resources2)
      Sums two resources arrays passed as inputs, if one is null returns the other. If both null, returns null. In any case, the returned array will be sorted.
      Parameters:
      resources1 - first array to be summed
      resources2 - second array to be summed
      Returns:
      the sum between resources1 and resources2
